Title: Series: Cabinet du Roy
Description: The flight into Egypt: landscape with river running into right foreground and, on the left, the Holy Family walking on a meandering path and turning left; after a drawing by an artist from the circle of Titian Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Anne Claude Philippe de Tubières, Comte de Caylus
Curator's comments: From 'Cabinet du Roy', see 1965,0319.2.1 for comment on the set and on the album. The original drawing (Département des Arts Graphiques, Louvre, Inv. 5540) is now attributed to an artist from the circle of Titian, rather than to the Venitian master himself
Bibliographic references: IFF / Inventaire du Fonds Français: Bibliothèque Nationale, Département des Estampes (431)
